<p>
  Please provide the path to the file you wish to upload. This should be relative to the root of your Dropbox folder. 
</p>
<p>
  e.g. For a file named <strong>'your-file-name.mbox'</strong>, in the folder <strong>'artsapi-uploads'</strong> located at the root of your dropbox, the location will be: <strong>'/artsapi-uploads/your-file-name.mbox'</strong>. 
</p>
<p>
  Note that ArtsAPI expects files in the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mbox" target='_blank'>mbox</a> format, so your file should have an .mbox extension, or be called <strong>mbox</strong> within a containing folder, i.e. <strong>'/containing-folder/mbox'</strong>. Different email clients will export to mbox in different ways, so make sure your upload follows one of the two patterns.
</p>

<hr>

<%= form_tag('/create_client_and_fetch_file', method: :post, class: 'width-50', remote: true) do %>

  <div class="form-group">
    <%= label_tag :location, 'File location:' %>
    <%= text_field_tag :location, '', class: 'form-control' %>
  </div>

  <div class="form-group">
    <%= check_box_tag :mine_keywords, 1, true %>
    <%= label_tag :mine_keywords, 'Mine keywords from email contents (Recommended)?' %>
  </div>

  <%= submit_tag 'Upload', class: 'btn btn-lg btn-primary', data: { disable_with: "Upload scheduled" } %>

<% end %>

<p class='margin-top-10'>
  <%= link_to "&larr; Return home while upload completes".html_safe, root_path %>
</p>